<rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>Jason Meridth's Blog (networking)</title><link>http://blog.jasonmeridth.com/</link><description></description><atom:link href="http://blog.jasonmeridth.com/categories/networking.xml" type="application/rss+xml" rel="self"></atom:link><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 05 Mar 2014 18:06:23 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>Nikola &lt;http://getnikola.com/&gt;</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>Renew DHCP Lease on Ubuntu VM After Moving Between Wireless Networks</title><link>http://blog.jasonmeridth.com/posts/renew-dhcp-lease-on-ubuntu-vm-after-moving-between-wireless-networks/</link><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;TL;DR&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;sudo dhclient -r &lt;span class="o"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;eth0&lt;span class="o"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; &amp;amp;amp;&amp;amp;amp; sudo dhclient &lt;span class="o"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;eth0&lt;span class="o"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I add that command as an alias to my ~/.bashrc file&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;alias &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nv"&gt;resetdhcp&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s1"&gt;'sudo dhclient -r eth0 &amp;amp;amp;&amp;amp;amp; sudo dhclient eth0'&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;then resourced it so I could use it in the bash session I was in&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;source&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;~/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;bashrc&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I constantly have my Ubuntu VM (VirtualBox) running on my Windows laptop and dock/undock it between work and home. Obviously those are two different wireless networks. Well, I was unable to find a dhcp renewal command that would work until today (look above).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This command releases and renews your DHCP IP Address.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Iâ€™m very happy about this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://linux.about.com/library/cmd/blcmdl8_dhclient.htm"&gt;dhclient man page&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When run by itself, your instance will seek out a new ip lease.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>ubuntu</category><category>networking</category><category>wireless</category><guid>http://blog.jasonmeridth.com/posts/renew-dhcp-lease-on-ubuntu-vm-after-moving-between-wireless-networks/</guid><pubDate>Tue, 05 Feb 2013 06:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>